## 🚀 Quick Start (5 Minutes)

### Prerequisites

- Python 3.10+ or Docker
- API Keys: Anthropic (Claude), Telegram Bot, optional MCP-Prompts server
- PostgreSQL 13+ and Redis 7+

### Option 1: Docker Compose (Recommended)

```bash
# Clone repository
git clone https://github.com/sparesparrow/scaipot.git
cd scaipot

# Copy environment template
cp .env.example .env

# Edit .env with your API keys
nano .env

# Start full stack
docker-compose up -d

# Initialize database
docker-compose exec scaipot python -m scaipot.cli init

# Check status
docker-compose ps
docker-compose logs -f scaipot
```

### Option 2: Local Development

```bash
# Clone and navigate
git clone https://github.com/sparesparrow/scaipot.git
cd scaipot

# Create virtual environment
python3.10 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

# Install dependencies
pip install -e ".[dev]"

# Copy and configure environment
cp .env.example .env
nano .env

# Run tests
pytest tests/ -v

# Start honeypot
python -m scaipot.cli start
```

### First Honeypot Deployment

```bash
# Create a Bitcoin investment honeypot for Telegram
python -m scaipot.cli create-honeypot \
  --platform telegram \
  --category bitcoin_investment \
  --name "BTCNewbie"

# Monitor incoming messages (logs to console + database)
tail -f logs/scaipot.log
```

